docs.abstract: The true message of the death and rebirth of Jesus.
docs.snippet: The true message of the death and rebirth of Jesus.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Easter Sunday, billions of Christians gather together to celebrate the event that’s indispensable to the Christian faith — the resurrection of Jesus Christ. As the Apostle Paul wrote to the church in Corinth, without the resurrection our faith is useless. The Easter focus on the resurrection is profoundly encouraging for people of Christian faith.

headline.main: Easter Rebukes the Christian Will to Power

docs.abstract: A conservation effort has worked well enough that there is now talk of sending some tigers to Cambodia to help that nation revive its own wild population.
docs.snippet: A conservation effort has worked well enough that there is now talk of sending some tigers to Cambodia to help that nation revive its own wild population.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the early 1970s, things looked grim for India’s tigers. A wild population estimated in the tens of thousands at the time of independence in 1947 had shrunk to around 1,800. The tigers’ decline also held worrying implications for the nation’s environment because the apex predator is part of a complex but fragile ecosystem. Something had to be done.

headline.main: Dangerously Scarce 50 Years Ago, India’s Tigers Bounce Back

docs.abstract: Galas were held for the New York Academy of Art and the Fashion Scholarship Fund.
docs.snippet: Galas were held for the New York Academy of Art and the Fashion Scholarship Fund.
docs.lead_paragraph: It may be the best art deal in town. The New York Academy of Art held its annual Tribeca Ball on April 4, where established collectors got to roam the art studios upstairs and buy work from 100 current students. Afterward, guests sat down for a filet mignon dinner that honored Amy Sherald, the figurative painter best known for her official portrait of Michelle Obama.

headline.main: What Brooke Shields Wore on the Town
headline.print_headline: A Ball Here, A Gala There

docs.abstract: A dialect from the state’s earliest Spanish-speaking settlers has endured for over 400 years in the state’s remote mountain villages. But its time may be running out.
docs.snippet: A dialect from the state’s earliest Spanish-speaking settlers has endured for over 400 years in the state’s remote mountain villages. But its time may be running out.
docs.lead_paragraph: QUESTA, N.M. — When the old regulars gather at Cynthia Rael-Vigil’s coffee shop in Questa, N.M., a village nestled in the snow-capped Sangre de Cristo Mountains, they sip lattes and lavender lemonade and gossip in Spanish.

headline.main: New Mexico Is Losing a Form of Spanish Spoken Nowhere Else on Earth

docs.abstract: In the year since El Salvador declared a state of emergency, the government has delivered a stunning blow to the gangs that were once the ultimate authority in much of the country.
docs.snippet: In the year since El Salvador declared a state of emergency, the government has delivered a stunning blow to the gangs that were once the ultimate authority in much of the country.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the MS-13 gang ran the neighborhood of Las Margaritas, one of its strongholds in El Salvador, there were rules you had to follow to stay alive.

headline.main: El Salvador Decimated Its Ruthless Gangs. But at What Cost?

docs.abstract: Probably not, experts say, given the shrunken state of its military industrial sector. A look at a major munitions maker helps explain why.
docs.snippet: Probably not, experts say, given the shrunken state of its military industrial sector. A look at a major munitions maker helps explain why.
docs.lead_paragraph: The giant robot arms and high-tech heaters at one of Europe’s largest ammunition plants have been whirring around the clock since the start of the war in Ukraine to produce more desperately needed 155-millimeter artillery shells. If all goes as planned, the factory’s parent company, Nammo, will be turning out as many as 200,000 of the shells a year by 2028 — up to 20 times more than its prewar production.

headline.main: Europe Has Pledged a Million Shells for Ukraine in a Year. Can It Deliver?
